Uses number theory to adjust the multiplier based on d=Zgcd⁡(Y,Z)d = \frac{Z}{\gcd(Y,Z)}d=gcd(Y,Z)Z​. This avoids unnecessary iterations.




**Approach 2 (Iterative Checking):**

Iteratively checks each multiple of Y{Y}Y starting from the first valid candidate until one meets the conditions.




**Approach 3 (Condensed Direct Computation):**

A compact version of Approach 1 combining the logic into fewer lines.



